{'text': "There's a lot of wasted potential in our young people. We have to put a lot of effort into helping them avoid the ruinous effects that drugs have on their lives."}
{'text': "The only thing we could do at this point in time is to decriminalize marijuana (which is already decriminalized in South Korea). We don't need to legalize drugs."}
{'text': 'The only reason to legalize drugs is if you want to treat addiction as a health and mental health problem, not a criminal one.'}
{'text': "It's important to recognize that we don't know enough about the long-term effects of legalizing drugs."}
{'text': 'It would be great if we could legalize drugs in small doses, like one to two grams, for medical use.'}
{'text': 'On the other hand, if we legalize drugs, the government will have no choice but to regulate the flow of drugs into the country.'}
{'text': "If we legalize drugs, we'll soon see an increase in drug deaths. This will lead to an increased demand for drugs, and an increase in drug cartels."}
{'text': 'We need to legalize drugs because the prohibition does not work. \xa0We should legalize drugs because it will decrease drug-related crime and drug-related deaths.'}

{'text': "We should also legalize the sale of alcoholic beverages. It doesn't make sense that the government should be in charge of making sure people don't drink and drive, but they're allowed to sell alcohol."}

{'text': "If you legalized drugs tomorrow, how would you make sure the people who get addicted to drugs didn't get addicted to something else, like alcohol or cigarettes?"}

{'text': "As long as we do not legalize the illegal trade of drugs, we'll always have a black market."}
{'text': "We don't need legalization of all drugs. \xa0We don't need any drugs at all. We don't need to legalize any drugs."}
{'text': '5. It will lead to more traffic accidents. The evidence seems to indicate that legalizing drugs will result in more traffic accidents.'}
{'text': "To be fair, I don't really understand why legalizing drugs is better than legalizing alcohol and tobacco, but I do agree with the legitimacy of the argument."}
{'text': 'The bigger issue with legalizing drugs is not that there are no negative effects, but rather that there are too many negative effects.'}
{'text': "If you legalize drugs, why can't you also legalize possession of drugs? If possession of drugs is legal, people will no longer be tempted to use them."}
{'text': "If we legalize drugs, what do we have to worry about when it comes to addiction and depression and schizophrenia? If we legalized alcohol, we wouldn't have to worry about drunk drivers."}
{'text': 'The legalization of drugs would only create a black market, since drug cartels would make money from the legalization of drugs.'}
{'text': "It's going to be impossible to control the drug use if you legalize them. \xa0That being said, I would prefer to see a complete eradication of drugs rather than legalize them."}

{'text': "Legalizing drugs would put the government in the position of being in charge of your personal health, because the government would be in charge of your health, your family's health, your partner's health,..."}
{'text': "Why don't we legalize all illegal substances? Even if we legalized all illegal substances, it would still lead to a lot of problems."}
{'text': 'People who do drugs, and people who are addicted to drugs, should not be allowed to drive.'}

{'text': 'By legalizing drugs, we could remove a lot of the criminal elements from the drug market, which would certainly make it easier to control them.'}
{'text': "The point is that there should be a minimum age at which people are allowed to use drugs. This age shouldn't be high. It shouldn't be less than eighteen."}
